com.exlibris.dps.sdk.plugin

Interface StartUpCheckPlugin


  • public interface StartUpCheckPlugin
    Interface for the StartUpCheck plugin type.
    The plugin executes a start up check on the system.
    All active start up check plugin instances are executed either when the server is started or as a scheduled job.
    This plugin interface supports both java and script implementation. For more information please refer to the User Guide.

      • execute

        boolean execute()
        Executes the plugins start up check
        Returns:
        true if the execution was successful, false otherwise

      • getSeverity

        StartUpCheckPlugin.Severity getSeverity()
        Returns the severity level of the plugin should the system check fail.
        Should the system check fail, a FATAL severity level plugin will generate a UI error message.
        Returns:
        The severity level of the plugin

      • getErrorMessage

        java.lang.String getErrorMessage()
        Returns:
        The error message created if the system check fails, null otherwise.

      • getRole

        StartUpCheckPlugin.ROLE[] getRole()
        Returns the roles that are relevant to this system check.
        The roles represent different distributing servers:
        DEP- deposit server
        REP- repository server
        DEL- delivery server
        PER- permanent server
        ALL- all servers
        Returns:
        An array of relevant roles

      • getCheckType

        java.lang.String getCheckType()
        Returns:
        The plugin type name of the system check
